<P>SOme Typographical Errors have cr<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">pt into the Pre&s;s&punc; which the Reader would be plea&s;ed to correct, as page 7. We &s;aw, lege when we &s;aw. page 38. my Lord D<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">r<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">n, lege my Lord Dar|ly or Darnly. p 94. Hilesha, leg Hildesha. Upon the head of the Pages, 137, till 146, a De&s;cription of Zetland, lege a De|&s;cription of Pightland Firth. Some other &s;mall Errata's there are, which the Candid Reader will pardon, &s;eeing in &s;o far as I ob&s;erve, they do not marr the &s;en&s;e.</P>
