<P>Tho the General Current of the Tide be &s;till the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">e, from We&s;t to Ea&s;t in a Flood,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Some &s;trange Re|ma<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ks a|bout the Tides.</NOTE> and from Ea&s;t to <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">e&s;t in an Ebb, yet running with violence upon the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">nd, they cau&s;e a contrary motion in the Sea next to <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> which they call <HI>Easter</HI> or <HI>We&s;ter Birth,</HI> according to Cour&s;e. And there are &s;ome things which have been <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">&s;erved as very &s;trange in the running of the Tides, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> that it flows two hours &s;ooner on the We&s;t &s;ide of <HI><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">nda</HI> then it doth on the Ea&s;t: And at <HI>Hammone&s;s</HI> in <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">e &s;ame <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">&s;le, both Ebb and Flood runns one way ex|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">pt at the b<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ginning of a quick &s;tream, when for 2 or 3 <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ures the Flood runs South; in <HI>North Faira</HI> the Sea
